Heat 2 Tbsp. of the dressing in large skillet on medium heat. Add chicken; cook and stir 5 min. or until cooked through. Add remaining 2 Tbsp. dressing, 1-1/2 cups water, chicken broth, soy sauce and peanut butter; mix well. Bring to a boil. Add spaghetti; cover. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 5 min. Stir in broccoli and carrots; cover. Simmer 4 to 6 min. or until spaghetti is tender. Serve immediately. Or, cover and refrigerate to serve chilled.